In a press briefing, White House spokesperson Karine Jean-Pierre discussed a range of topics. John Kirby from the National Security Council provided information about actions being taken to counter the Russian private military company known as Wagner. The Department of Treasury will designate Wagner as a significant Transnational Criminal Organization and impose additional sanctions on the company and its support network. Kirby also discussed North Korea's support for Wagner and the ongoing conflict in Ukraine. Jean-Pierre mentioned that Vice President Kamala Harris will be delivering a speech on abortion rights in Tallahassee, Florida, and emphasized the administration's commitment to protecting women's rights. She also mentioned that President Joe Biden will be hosting Democratic Congressional leaders at the White House and delivering remarks on the economy.